Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, former first lady Dr. Patience Jonathan, national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu are among the dignitaries honouring the First Lady, Aisha Buhari at the presentation of her book, “Aisha Buhari, Being Different.” Other dignitaries include Deputy President of the Senate, Ovie Omo-Agege and the former Minister of Niger Delta Affairs under President Goodluck Jonathan, Godsday Orubebe. Also present at the event chaired by Asiwaju Tinubu are the Ooni of Ife, Imperial Majesty, Adeyeye Ogunwusi, the Sultan of Sokoto, His Eminence, Sa’ad Abubakar III, wife of former Vice President, Amina Sambo and Chairman of Nigeria Governors Forum, NGF and Governor of Ekiti State, Dr. Kayode Fayemi among others. The book, authored by Hajo Sani, Senior Special Assistant to the President on Administration and Women Affairs is being launched at the old Banquet Hall in the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Details later.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .